data.description:
Three-Story Home & Duplex Included in Price!  You will be stunned when you enter the Historic Carson Mansion in Coalgate, Oklahoma!  This magnificent home was built in 1903, and completely rebuilt and modernized from the foundation up in 1995 but still has vintage features like original oak mantle and mirror, clawfoot tub, pocket doors, vintage light fixtures and switches and the third floor retains the 4 large oval shaped gable windows!
 
5  bedrooms/ 3.5 baths - first floor has 1 bed & 1.5 baths; 2nd floor has 4 bedrooms, 2 baths and sitting area; 3rd floor has custom oak spiral staircase and wet bar.  Stunning oak floors, built-in bookshelves, stairwells, doors & woodwork throughout!  New in 1995:  foundation, brick exterior, skylights, plumbing, electrical panels and wiring, heat pumps, hot water heater, wood burning fireplace in master bedroom, fireplace in den with wood stove insert and pass-through wood storage closet...and so much more!!!
 
Wrap around porch leads to one-of-a-kind gazebo ready for early morning coffee or late afternoon tea!  Huge cellar, brick storage building, oversized two car garage...you really have to see it!!!
 
This has been a private residence, but would make a wonderful Bed & Breakfast.  Plus, the adjacent duplex that's included in the price, could be converted into cottages to add more rental space to Bed & Breakfast!
data.whatILove: Large, comfortable home built with extrordinary quality and craftsmanship, with many original charming period details.  Separate brick workshop or storage building could be converted into a stand alone office.
